Kwara State House of Assembly has urged Governor Abdulrahman Abdulrasaq to set machinery in motion for the implementation of the state’s Child Rights Law to ensure adequate protection of children in the state. This is part of the resolutions of the house following a motion, ‘Need to Implement the Kwara State Child’s Rights Law’, raised by House Leader and member representing Ilorin Central, Abubakar Mogaji.The Speaker, Yakubu Salihu, while reading the resolutions, explained that the need for the state government to commence its implementation became expedient in view of the urgent need to curb child abuse and other vices against the future leaders.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .